Board Approval - Concise.prompt_template:
Summarize the board approval status for the merger:

- Target Company Board: {target_approval}
- Target Unanimity: {target_unanimous}
- Parent Company Board: {acquirer_approval}
- Parent Unanimity: {acquirer_unanimous}
- Combine the above into a single concise statement regarding both the company and parent board approvals. Use legal language, and no words like however.
- If unanimous approval has not been granted by either of the parties simply state they have approval but it is not described as unanimous.

--- Examples
Merger has been unanimously approved by the CLEG board; BMY board approval is not described as unanimous.
Merger has been unanimously approved by the X board; Nippon board approval is not described as unanimous.
Merger has been unanimously approved by the boards of AZEK and JHX.

